        <h1><span class="title" itemprop="name" data-bind="text:title">A Bit Crack</span></h1>
    </header>

    <img class="picture pull-right img-responsive" itemprop="image" data-fieldname="picture" src="/media/cache/55/c3/55c3b98863eb12bb833799dd6613a3c0.jpg" width="400" height="400" data-src="/static/img/events/filler.png" data-width="400" data-height="400" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#img-picture-789" alt="" data-bind="attr: { src: pictureData().displaySrc, width: pictureData().displayWidth, height: pictureData().displayHeight, 'data-src': pictureData().src, 'data-width': pictureData().width, 'data-height': pictureData().height }" /><div class="modal " id="img-picture-789">    <div class="modal-dialog">        <div class="modal-content">            <div class="modal-header">                <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">                    &times;                </button>            </div>            <div class="modal-body">                <img src="/static/img/events/filler.png" class="img-responsive" alt="" data-bind="attr: {src: pictureData().displaySrc}">            </div>        </div>    </div></div>

    <h3><time class="startDateTime" itemprop="startDate" datetime="2007-12-07 19:30:00+00:00" data-bind="attr:{datetime:startDateTime()},text:displayStart()">7:30 p.m.</time> to <time class="endDateTime" itemprop="endDate" datetime="2007-12-07 22:00:00+00:00" data-bind="attr:{datetime:endDateTime()},text:displayEnd()">10:00 p.m. Friday 7 December 2007</time></h3>

    <meta itemprop="image" content="/media/cache/55/c3/55c3b98863eb12bb833799dd6613a3c0.jpg">

    <div class="bodysection">
        <div class="body" itemprop="about" data-fieldname="body" data-bind="htmlValue:body">Storytelling evening: Tales of Solomon and Sheba.Special storrytelling evening, with Sally Pomme Clayton, one of Britain's best-loved storytellers. <p><strong></strong></p><p class="callout"><strong>Tales of Solomon and Sheba</strong></p><p>The Queen of Sheba is provocative, seductive and a virgin. She visits King Solomon to test <img alt="sally pomme" class="image-right" height="223" src="/static/image/import/y342zg7lpftu1qboka0m.jpg" width="148" />his wisdom. Riddles and tricks, desire and foolishness ensue as they unravel each other's histories. </p><p>Tonight, <strong>Sally Pomme Clayton</strong> (photo) will be telling us stories from Sumerian, Hebrew, Christian and Muslim traditions. She will conjure the powerful archetypes of Solomon and Sheba. This vibrant and dynamic performance is told with an ancient Ethiopian story scroll.</p><p class="callout">DOUBLE BILL WITH FILM ON THU 6 DEC&hellip;</p><p><strong><a href="/ss_film.2007-11-29.3935483241/">The Heritage of the Griot</a>,</strong> from Burkina Faso has been programmed in partnership with A Bit Crack storytelling guest, Sally Pomme Clayton. Sally chose this film in homage to the long history of spoken storytelling that pre-exists the written word. </p><p><strong>SPECIAL DOUBLE TICKET: £7/6 for this event and A Bit Crack on Dec 7 (or £4/3 for the film, and £6/£4 for the storytelling evening)</strong> </p><p>7.30 pm on the First Friday each month Storytelling at the Star &amp; Shadow <a href="http://www.abitcrack.com/">http://www.abitcrack.com/</a></p></div>
    </div>

